        <h3>Guest User Implementation</h3>
        <div style="background-color: #e3f2fd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 15px 0; border-left: 4px solid #2196f3;">
            <p><strong>Method:</strong> <code>_ensure_user_session()</code> in AI.pm (lines 250-280)</p>
            <p><strong>Behavior:</strong> When unauthenticated user accesses AI endpoints, system automatically creates/assigns user_id=199 (guest user)</p>
            <p><strong>Result:</strong> All conversations and messages are properly recorded to database under guest account</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Known Issues Identified (Dec 31 Audit)</h3>
        <div style="background-color: #ffebee; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 15px 0; border-left: 4px solid #d32f2f;">
            <strong>⚠️ BLOCKING ISSUE:</strong> Conversation records NOT being created despite code being present
            <ul style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0;">
                <li><strong>Symptom:</strong> AiConversation and AiMessage records not appearing in database</li>
                <li><strong>Code Status:</strong> Creation code exists (AI.pm lines 387-407, 425-435) with error checking</li>
                <li><strong>Likely Cause:</strong> Table naming convention mismatch (Result files may declare wrong table names)</li>
                <li><strong>Verification Needed:</strong> Run database verification queries (see Next Steps below)</li>
                <li><strong>Impact:</strong> Chat history not persisting; users cannot see previous conversations</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
